fference(self, nums: List[int]) -> int:\n        # Sort the array to find the two largest and two smallest numbers\n        nums.sort()\n        \n        # The two largest numbers will be the last two elements\n        max1, max2 = nums[-1], nums[-2]\n        \n        # The two smallest numbers will be the first two elements\n        min1, min2 = nums[0], nums[1]\n        \n        # Calculate the product difference\n        product_difference = (max1 * max2) - (min1 * min2)\n        \n        return product_difference\n```\n\nThis solution sorts the array to easily identify the two largest and two smallest numbers, which are used to compute the maximum product difference. The time complexity of this approach is O(n log n) due to the sorting step. Given the constraints, this is efficient enough.", "estimated_date": 1624752000000}